Messages from Midgard #10 - Deadpool Down Under. Get the scoop from the war (of the realms) front courtesy of @midnighterbae #comics #comicbooks #waroftherealms #marvel

“War of the Realms” is starting to wind down this week with the release of the penultimate issue of the core series, War of the Realms #5. The comic has a predictable ending thanks to the marketing department, but actually feels like a Jason Aaron/Russell Dauterman/Matthew Wilson Thor comic thanks to its excellent characterization of Thor and Jane Foster to go with fight scenes a lathe third act…

summary: I can’t even begin to say how happy I am that young girls and women get to see Captain Marvel. The other day, a random man on...
body:
I can’t even begin to say how happy I am that young girls and women get to see Captain Marvel. The other day, a random man on the street motioned me over to him, and when I said no, he smiled. I had to look around in fear for the next thirty minutes to make sure he wasn’t following me or my sisters.

If I had Carol’s power, I would do exactly what she’s doing - saving worlds, from ending wars to putting verbal harassers on their knees as a warning and a statement. She is showing us all that our passion and anger are our strengths and those strengths cannot be taken by anyone under any circumstances.

Thank you, Brie Larson, and thank you, Carol Danvers. You’re both making the MCU and our reality a better place, and even if the fear is there, you’re helping us realize more and more just how much power we own within ourselves.
